        <p>The truth is, your fatigue isn't about age‚Äîit's about <strong>energy production at the cellular level</strong>.</p>

        <p>Every cell in your body contains tiny structures called <strong>mitochondria</strong>. Think of them as microscopic power plants that convert the food you eat into energy your body can use.</p>

        <p>Here's the problem: <strong>After age 40, your mitochondria start producing less energy</strong>. Much less.</p>

