        <h2>The NAD Connection: Your Body's Master Energy Molecule</h2>

        <p>At the heart of mitochondrial function is a molecule called <strong>NAD (Nicotinamide Adenine Dinucleotide)</strong>.</p>

        <p>NAD is like the spark plug that ignites energy production in your cells. Without adequate NAD, your mitochondria literally can't make energy efficiently.</p>

        <p>Here's the kicker: <strong>NAD levels plummet after age 40</strong>. By the time you're 60, you have roughly half the NAD you had in your 20s.</p>

        <div class="highlight">
            <h3>üî• The NAD Discovery That Changes Everything</h3>
